notesStmt.note: First few leaves badly damaged, inlaid before rebinding.
Slight damp and tidemarks at edges. Mould damage at edges.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 25; written lines: 25; Uniform layout. Visible ruling with mastara. Initial words and terms highlighted in red ink. Catchwords on every verso. Marginal notes and additions.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite semi-cursive script of the 15th century.
